21/09/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Parliament adopted a declaration Friday (19 September) stating its resolve to promote and strengthen ties with the United States. The document also stipulates the country's commitment to conduct necessary reforms on the way to NATO entry and to participate in the international community's efforts to restore peace and begin post-war reconstruction in different regions. The declaration was adopted on the occasion of the 100th anniversary of the establishment of Bulgarian-US diplomatic relations. (BTA, BNT, bTV - 19/09/03)
